    markdown:
      "## create_reversal\n\n`client.ledgerTransactions.createReversal(id: string, description?: string, effective_at?: string, external_id?: string, ledgerable_id?: string, ledgerable_type?: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal', metadata?: object, status?: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'): { id: string; archived_reason: string; created_at: string; description: string; effective_at: string; effective_date: string; external_id: string; ledger_entries: ledger_entry[]; ledger_id: string; ledgerable_id: string; ledgerable_type: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; partially_posts_ledger_transaction_id: string; posted_at: string; reversed_by_ledger_transaction_id: string; reverses_ledger_transaction_id: string; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; updated_at: string; }`\n\n**post** `/api/ledger_transactions/{id}/reversal`\n\nCreate a ledger transaction reversal.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `id: string`\n\n- `description?: string`\n  An optional free-form description for the reversal ledger transaction. Maximum of 1000 characters allowed.\n\n- `effective_at?: string`\n  The timestamp (ISO8601 format) at which the reversal ledger transaction happened for reporting purposes. It defaults to the `effective_at` of the original ledger transaction if not provided.\n\n- `external_id?: string`\n  Must be unique within the ledger.\n\n- `ledgerable_id?: string`\n  Specify this if you'd like to link the reversal ledger transaction to a Payment object like Return or Reversal.\n\n- `ledgerable_type?: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'`\n  Specify this if you'd like to link the reversal ledger transaction to a Payment object like Return or Reversal.\n\n- `metadata?: object`\n  Additional data to be added to the reversal ledger transaction as key-value pairs. Both the key and value must be strings.\n\n- `status?: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'`\n  Status of the reversal ledger transaction. It defaults to `posted` if not provided.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; archived_reason: string; created_at: string; description: string; effective_at: string; effective_date: string; external_id: string; ledger_entries: { id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; direction: transaction_direction; discarded_at: string; effective_at: string; ledger_account_currency: string; ledger_account_currency_exponent: number; ledger_account_id: string; ledger_account_lock_version: number; ledger_transaction_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; resulting_ledger_account_balances: ledger_balances; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; updated_at: string; }[]; ledger_id: string; ledgerable_id: string; ledgerable_type: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; partially_posts_ledger_transaction_id: string; posted_at: string; reversed_by_ledger_transaction_id: string; reverses_ledger_transaction_id: string; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; updated_at: string; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `archived_reason: string`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `description: string`\n  - `effective_at: string`\n  - `effective_date: string`\n  - `external_id: string`\n  - `ledger_entries: { id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; direction: 'credit' | 'debit'; discarded_at: string; effective_at: string; ledger_account_currency: string; ledger_account_currency_exponent: number; ledger_account_id: string; ledger_account_lock_version: number; ledger_transaction_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; resulting_ledger_account_balances: { available_balance: ledger_balance; pending_balance: ledger_balance; posted_balance: ledger_balance; }; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; updated_at: string; }[]`\n  - `ledger_id: string`\n  - `ledgerable_id: string`\n  - `ledgerable_type: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'`\n  - `live_mode: boolean`\n  - `metadata: object`\n  - `object: string`\n  - `partially_posts_ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `posted_at: string`\n  - `reversed_by_ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `reverses_ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'`\n  - `updated_at: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport ModernTreasury from 'modern-treasury';\n\nconst client = new ModernTreasury();\n\nconst ledgerTransaction = await client.ledgerTransactions.createReversal('id');\n\nconsole.log(ledgerTransaction);\n```",
