    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.paymentOrders.reversals.create(payment_order_id: string, reason: string, ledger_transaction?: { ledger_entries: ledger_entry_create_request[]; description?: string; effective_at?: string; effective_date?: string; external_id?: string; ledgerable_id?: string; ledgerable_type?: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'; metadata?: object; status?: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; }, metadata?: object): { id: string; created_at: string; internal_account_id: string; ledger_transaction_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; payment_order_id: string; reason: string; reconciliation_status: 'unreconciled' | 'tentatively_reconciled' | 'reconciled'; status: 'cancelled' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'pending' | 'processing' | 'returned' | 'sent'; transaction_ids: string[]; updated_at: string; }`\n\n**post** `/api/payment_orders/{payment_order_id}/reversals`\n\nCreate a reversal for a payment order.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `payment_order_id: string`\n  The id of the payment order being reversed.\n\n- `reason: string`\n  The reason for the reversal. Must be one of `duplicate`, `incorrect_amount`, `incorrect_receiving_account`, `date_earlier_than_intended`, `date_later_than_intended`.\n\n- `ledger_transaction?: { ledger_entries: { amount: number; direction: transaction_direction; ledger_account_id: string; available_balance_amount?: object; effective_at?: string; lock_version?: number; metadata?: object; pending_balance_amount?: object; posted_balance_amount?: object; show_resulting_ledger_account_balances?: boolean; }[]; description?: string; effective_at?: string; effective_date?: string; external_id?: string; ledgerable_id?: string; ledgerable_type?: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'; metadata?: object; status?: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; }`\n  Specifies a ledger transaction object that will be created with the reversal. If the ledger transaction cannot be created, then the reversal creation will fail. The resulting ledger transaction will mirror the status of the reversal.\n  - `ledger_entries: { amount: number; direction: 'credit' | 'debit'; ledger_account_id: string; available_balance_amount?: object; effective_at?: string; lock_version?: number; metadata?: object; pending_balance_amount?: object; posted_balance_amount?: object; show_resulting_ledger_account_balances?: boolean; }[]`\n    An array of ledger entry objects.\n  - `description?: string`\n    An optional description for internal use.\n  - `effective_at?: string`\n    The timestamp (ISO8601 format) at which the ledger transaction happened for reporting purposes.\n  - `effective_date?: string`\n    The date (YYYY-MM-DD) on which the ledger transaction happened for reporting purposes.\n  - `external_id?: string`\n    A unique string to represent the ledger transaction. Only one pending or posted ledger transaction may have this ID in the ledger.\n  - `ledgerable_id?: string`\n    If the ledger transaction can be reconciled to another object in Modern Treasury, the id will be populated here, otherwise null.\n  - `ledgerable_type?: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'`\n    If the ledger transaction can be reconciled to another object in Modern Treasury, the type will be populated here, otherwise null. This can be one of payment_order, incoming_payment_detail, expected_payment, return, or reversal.\n  - `metadata?: object`\n    Additional data represented as key-value pairs. Both the key and value must be strings.\n  - `status?: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'`\n    To post a ledger transaction at creation, use `posted`.\n\n- `metadata?: object`\n  Additional data represented as key-value pairs. Both the key and value must be strings.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; created_at: string; internal_account_id: string; ledger_transaction_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; payment_order_id: string; reason: string; reconciliation_status: 'unreconciled' | 'tentatively_reconciled' | 'reconciled'; status: 'cancelled' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'pending' | 'processing' | 'returned' | 'sent'; transaction_ids: string[]; updated_at: string; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `internal_account_id: string`\n  - `ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `live_mode: boolean`\n  - `metadata: object`\n  - `object: string`\n  - `payment_order_id: string`\n  - `reason: string`\n  - `reconciliation_status: 'unreconciled' | 'tentatively_reconciled' | 'reconciled'`\n  - `status: 'cancelled' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'pending' | 'processing' | 'returned' | 'sent'`\n  - `transaction_ids: string[]`\n  - `updated_at: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport ModernTreasury from 'modern-treasury';\n\nconst client = new ModernTreasury();\n\nconst reversal = await client.paymentOrders.reversals.create('payment_order_id', { reason: 'duplicate' });\n\nconsole.log(reversal);\n```",
